Package org.jlab.jaws.eventsource

Interface EventSourceListener<K,​V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - The type for message keys
    V - The type for message values
    public interface EventSourceListener<K,​V>
    An EventSourceListener can be registered to receive batch-processing call-backs from an EventSourceTable. The first call-back is always the initial state of the database (up to the high water mark). Changes are reported in batches thereafter as a list of changes (duplicate keys possible).

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      default void changes​(List<EventSourceRecord<K,​V>> records)
      This callback is invoked periodically depending on EventSourceConfig.EVENT_SOURCE_POLL_MILLIS and EventSourceConfig.EVENT_SOURCE_MAX_POLL_BEFORE_FLUSH settings with changes that occur after the initial state.
      default void initialState​(Set<EventSourceRecord<K,​V>> records)
      This callback is invoked only once upon determination of initial state and contains the initial set of unique records up to high water mark (latest keys overwrite older keys).
